VShri Rama Kala Vedike is organising an exclusive music performance by flautist Pandit Hariprasad Chaurasia at Ravindra Kalakshetra on August 12, 6 p.m. Rama Kala Vedika will also felicitate Hariprasad Chaurasia, Dr. Gangubhai Hangal, and Sheshagiri Hangal for their contribution to music.The Governor of Karnataka, T.N.Chaturvedi will be the chief guest and felicitate the musicians.The founder of the forum, renowned tabla artiste Ravindra Yavagal, has set up Rama Kala Vedika in memory of his father, Ramachandra Yavagal.Ravindra Yavagal initially introduced a yearly all night music programme in 1978 at his residence in Hubli.Even after he joined the All India Radio in Bangalore he continued to arrange memorial concerts at his residence.Encouraged by the response, Yavagal, along with his students and friends, established Shri Rama Kala Vedike, a forum of fine arts in the year 2000.The Vedike plans to organise three music programmes a year, award scholarships to music students, conduct music workshops by senior artistes, establish fulltime school for tabla and conduct art exhibitions.In 2005, the Vedike instituted a scholarship for child prodigies and the Kala Shringa award for senior musicians in memory of Ramachandra Yavagal.Bottom Template Starts
